      "title": "1.0 Series",
      "type": "Section"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "IPython 1.0 requires Python \u2265 2.6.5 or \u2265 3.2.1. It does not support Python 3.0, 3.1, or 2.5."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "This is a big release.  The principal milestone is the addition of "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "IPython.nbconvert"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": ", but there has been a great deal of work improving all parts of IPython as well."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The previous version (0.13) was released on June 30, 2012, and in this development cycle we had:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "~12 months of work."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "~700 pull requests merged."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "~600 issues closed (non-pull requests)."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "contributions from ~150 authors."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "~4000 commits."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            }
          ],
          "ordered": false,
          "spread": false,
          "start": 1,
          "type": "list"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The amount of work included in this release is so large that we can only cover here the main highlights; please see our "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "detailed release statistics\n<issues_list_100>"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " for links to every issue and pull request closed on GitHub as well as a full list of individual contributors. It includes"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "level": 1,
      "target": null,
      "title": "Release 1.0.0: An Afternoon Hack",
      "type": "Section"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "There have been two major reorganizations in IPython 1.0:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "Added "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "IPython.kernel"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": " for all kernel-related code.   This means that "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "IPython.zmq"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": " has been removed,   and much of it is now in "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "IPython.kernel.zmq"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": ",   some of it being in the top-level "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "IPython.kernel"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "We have removed the "
                    },
                    {
                      "domain": null,
                      "role": null,
                      "type": "Directive",
                      "value": "frontend"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": " subpackage,   as it caused unnecessary depth.  So what was "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "IPython.frontend.qt"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "   is now "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "IPython.qt"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": ", and so on.  The one difference is that   the notebook has been further flattened, so that   "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "IPython.frontend.html.notebook"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": " is now just "
                    },
                    {
                      "domain": null,
                      "role": null,
                      "type": "Directive",
                      "value": "IPython.html"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": ".   There is a shim module, so "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "IPython.frontend"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": " is still   importable in 1.0, but there will be a warning."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "The IPython sphinx directives are now installed in "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
                      "value": "IPython.sphinx"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": ",   so they can be imported by other projects."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "spread": false,
              "type": "listItem"
            }
          ],
          "ordered": false,
          "spread": false,
          "start": 1,
          "type": "list"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "target": null,
      "title": "Reorganization",
      "type": "Section"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "For the first time since 0.10 (sorry, everyone), there is an official public API for starting IPython:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "args": "python",
          "children": [],
          "name": "sourcecode",
          "options": {},
          "type": "mystDirective",
          "value": "from IPython import start_ipython\nstart_ipython()"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "This is what packages should use that start their own IPython session, but don't actually want embedded IPython (most cases). "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "IPython.embed()"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " is used for embedding IPython into the calling namespace, similar to calling "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "Pdb.set_trace"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": ", whereas "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "start_ipython"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " will start a plain IPython session, loading config and startup files as normal."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "We also have added:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "args": "python",
          "children": [],
          "name": "sourcecode",
          "options": {},
          "type": "mystDirective",
          "value": "from IPython import get_ipython"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Which is a "
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "library"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " function for getting the current IPython instance, and will return "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "None"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " if no IPython instance is running. This is the official way to check whether your code is called from inside an IPython session. If you want to check for IPython without unnecessarily importing IPython, use this function:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "args": "python",
          "children": [],
          "name": "sourcecode",
          "options": {},
          "type": "mystDirective",
          "value": "def get_ipython():\n    \"\"\"return IPython instance if there is one, None otherwise\"\"\"\n    import sys\n    if \"IPython\" in sys.modules:\n        import IPython\n        return IPython.get_ipython()"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "target": null,
      "title": "Public APIs",
      "type": "Section"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "value": "The input transformation framework has been reworked. This fixes some corner   cases, and adds more flexibility for projects which use IPython, like SymPy &   SAGE. For more details, see "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "inlineCode",
